first when you want to start with cypress you need to install Node js
Then you add the path of nodejs to environment variables to use npm command globally from the terminal.
open your project directory in Visual Studio Code terminal and run the following command to install Cypress:: npm install cypress --save-dev
this installs Cypress locally for your project and adds it to your node_modules.
the command to open cypress is: ./node_modules/.bin/cypress open or npx cypress open
cypress configuration: 
in the cypress.config.js file, you specify the folder where your test files are located: specPattern: 'cypress/integration/examples/*.js'